<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-02-19.1.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80063" speakername="Mr Kenny MacAskill (Lothians) (SNP)" spid="S2W-4853" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0219.htm#1" holdingdate="2004-01-15">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how much funding has been allocated under the concessionary fares scheme (a) since the scheme's inception and (b) for each of the next two years, broken down by local authority area.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-02-19.1.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80115" speakername="Nicol Stephen" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0219.htm#se_Minister">

  <p>The funding for the current concessionary travel schemes is allocated to local authorities primarily by formula allocation. The information requested is set out in the following tables.</p>

  <p>Funding for the partnership agreement commitments for a national free off-peak bus scheme for older people and people with disabilities, and for progressively introducing a scheme of national bus, rail and ferry concessionary travel for young people, initially for all in full time education and training, will be determined following the formal consultation process and the research and analysis which will be required to support the implementation of the commitments.</p>

